# nl-rag distilled facts — domain: bristol-channel-pilot-cutter
# one declarative sentence per line; load with:  neuron --db app.db import pack.facts --scope knowledge
[src:bristol-channel-pilot-cutter/24-25-vict-p01] This is a complete **list of acts of the Parliament of the United Kingdom for the years 1861**.
[src:bristol-channel-pilot-cutter/24-25-vict-p01] Note that the first parliament of the United Kingdom was held in 1801; parliaments between 1707 and 1800 were either parliaments of Great Britain or of Ireland).
[src:bristol-channel-pilot-cutter/24-25-vict-p01] For acts passed up until 1707, see the list of acts of the Parliament of England and the list of acts of the Parliament of Scotland.
[src:bristol-channel-pilot-cutter/24-25-vict-p01] For acts passed from 1707 to 1800, see the list of acts of the Parliament of Great Britain.
[src:bristol-channel-pilot-cutter/24-25-vict-p01] See also the list of acts of the Parliament of Ireland.
[src:bristol-channel-pilot-cutter/24-25-vict-p01] For acts of the devolved parliaments and assemblies in the United Kingdom, see the list of acts of the Scottish Parliament, the list of acts of the Northern Ireland Assembly, and the list of acts and measures of Senedd Cymru; see also the list of acts of the Parliament of Northern Ireland.
[src:bristol-channel-pilot-cutter/24-25-vict-p01] The number shown after each act's title is its chapter number.
[src:bristol-channel-pilot-cutter/24-25-vict-p01] Acts passed before 1963 are cited using this number, preceded by the year(s) of the reign during which the relevant parliamentary session was held; thus the Union with Ireland Act 1800 is cited as "39 & 40 Geo.
[src:bristol-channel-pilot-cutter/24-25-vict-p01] 67", meaning the 67th act passed during the session that started in the 39th year of the reign of George III and which finished in the 40th year of that reign.
[src:bristol-channel-pilot-cutter/24-25-vict-p01] Note that the modern convention is to use Arabic numerals in citations (thus "41 Geo.
[src:bristol-channel-pilot-cutter/24-25-vict-p01] Acts of the last session of the Parliament of Great Britain and the first session of the Parliament of the United Kingdom are both cited as "41 Geo.
[src:bristol-channel-pilot-cutter/24-25-vict-p01] Some of these acts have never had a short title.
[src:bristol-channel-pilot-cutter/24-25-vict-p01] Some of these acts have a short title given to them by later acts, such as by the Short Titles Act 1896.
[src:bristol-channel-pilot-cutter/24-25-vict-p01] The third session of the 18th Parliament of the United Kingdom, which met from 5 February 1861 until 6 August 1861.
[src:bristol-channel-pilot-cutter/24-25-vict-p01] An Act to authorize the Inclosure of certain Lands in pursuance of a Report of the Inclosure Commissioners for England and Wales.
